OL,3,CAnti-sewage campaigners turn-out for
OL,4,Cpaddle out protests
OL,6,FSurfers, swimmers and paddle-boarders
OL,7,Fhave taken part in protests at
OL,8,Fbeaches, rivers and lakes across Devon
OL,9,Fand Cornwall as part of an annual
OL,10,Fprotest against an "ongoing sewage
OL,11,Fcrisis."
OL,13,FThe Paddle Out Protests, led by
OL,14,FSurfers Against Sewage, took place at
OL,15,Fmore than 40 bathing sites across the
OL,16,FUK on Saturday, 17 May, including
OL,17,FExmouth, Croyde and Plymouth Hoe in
OL,18,FDevon, and Seaton, St Ives and Gylly
OL,19,FBeach in Cornwall.
